results.name: a(1)=1, a(2)=2, a(3)=3, a(n) = smallest positive integer not occurring earlier in sequence and coprime to a(n-1), a(n-2) and a(n-3).
comment: Conjectured to be not a permutation of the natural numbers.
_Charles R Greathouse IV_ extended this, and confirms that primes occur in natural order. - _Jonathan Vos Post_ and _M. F. Hasler_, Jan 18 2011

Conjecture: for n >= 67, a(n) is even if and only if n == 2 mod 4 and divisible by 3 if and only if n == 3 mod 4.  In particular, this implies the last value divisible by 6 is a(66) = 36. - _Robert Israel_, May 12 2015
